title: Poland Unemployment Rate
description: Unemployment Rate in Poland increased to 5.10 percent in September from 4.80 percent in August of 2022. Unemployment Rate in Poland averaged 12.03 percent from 1990 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 20.70 percent in February of 2003 and a record low of 0.30 percent in January of 1990. In Poland, the unemployment rate measures the number of people actively looking for a job as a percentage of the labour force. This page provides the latest reported value for - Poland Unemployment Rate - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: Central Statistical Office of Poland (GUS)
